
A production defines the web pages, data content, and behavior of a production.

Initially there will be 1 production per customer.

A production can only have one event in process at a time.

An event is an instance of a production - for example the Accounting dept monthly meeting

A MQTT production event is started 1 hour before each production and runs during the full period the production is broadcasting, and possibly some time after.  

Production names are designated as P1, P2, P3

Example production ids are the $CID: $CID_prod1, $CID_prod2, 

Each customer is assigned a two letter acronym called the CID 
   Use it to precede metrics -- IN_FILES



  
